N: react-bits
D: Integrate, customize, and contribute to react-bits, the creative animated React component library.
G: react-bits, animated components, gsap react, three fiber, tailwind v4, jsrepo
U:
- Install peer dependencies (gsap, motion, @react-three/fiber) in the target project before adding react-bits components.
- Use useGSAP or clean up GSAP timelines inside useLayoutEffect to prevent memory leaks in React Strict Mode.
- Scaffold new components using npm run new:component to maintain registry compatibility.
- Follow the feat/<feature-name> branch naming convention for all pull requests.
S:
- Identify the target component and its peer dependencies from the react-bits catalog.
- Install the required animation libraries (e.g., gsap, motion, @react-three/fiber) in the target project.
- Copy the component source code or use jsrepo to import it.
- Customize animation parameters (durations, eases, triggers) safely using React refs and lifecycle hooks.
- Validate the integration by testing component mount/unmount cycles to ensure no animation memory leaks.
R:
- package.json: Project dependencies (GSAP, Three.js, Tailwind v4) and scripts
- CONTRIBUTING.md: Branch naming conventions (feat/<feature-name>) and PR guidelines
- jsrepo.config.ts: Registry configuration for component distribution
